'''Roberto Carlos Lopes''' ({{IPA|pt|ʀu.ˈbɛ.tu ˈkaɾ.luʒ ˈlɔpɨʃ|lang}}; born 17 June 1992), also known as '''Pico''' ({{IPA|kea|ˈpi.ku|lang}}),<ref name="shamrockroversIEprofile">{{Cite web|url=https://www.shamrockrovers.ie/player/roberto-lopes/|title=Roberto Lopes|website=Shamrock Rovers | accessdate = 19 October 2019 }}</ref> is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Shamrock Rovers F.C.|Shamrock Rovers]].<ref name="shamrockroversIEprofile"/> Born in Ireland, he represents the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]].

==Club career==
===Shamrock Rovers===
In November 2016 Lopes joined [[Shamrock Rovers]] after leaving rivals [[Bohemian F.C.|Bohemians]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-ie/news/3909/airtricity-premier-division/2016/11/18/29635382/shamrock-rovers-sign-corry-connolly-lopes-devine|title=Shamrock Rovers sign Corry, Connolly, Lopes & Devine &#124; Goal.com|website=www.goal.com}}</ref>

Lopes became a regular starter for the hoops in the 2017 season.

In 2019, Lopes scored his first European goal vs [[Apollon Limassol]] with a header to make it 2–1. Lopes won the [[2019 FAI Cup|FAI Cup]] in 2019 where Rovers defeated [[Dundalk F.C.]] on penalties.

In 2020, Lopes was a member of the Shamrock Rovers squad that won the [[League of Ireland]] title. Lopes went on to win 3 more leagues in a row with Rovers.

In 2024, Lopes became captain of Rovers after [[Ronan Finn]] left the club. He captained them to the [[2024–25 UEFA Conference League]] playoff round, the first time an Irish club had reached the knockout stage of a European tournament.

In 2025 Lopes won the double as captain, Rovers first domestic double since 1987.

==International career==
[[File:Phase de match (cropped).jpg|thumb|Lopes with [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde]] at the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]]]]
Lopes was born in Ireland to a Cape Verdean father and Irish mother.<ref>{{cite web | last=Petrie | first=Richard | title=Roberto Lopes: World Cup-bound Cape Verde defender relishing his week to remember | website=BBC Sport | date=14 October 2025 | url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cz91wd87p41o | access-date=15 October 2025}}</ref> He made one appearance for the Republic of Ireland's under 19 squad in 2011.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/africa/59773218|title=Lopes set for Afcon after call-up via LinkedIn|work=BBC Sport }}</ref> Lopes made his international debut for the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]] in a 2–0 friendly win over [[Togo national football team|Togo]] in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://africa.espn.com/football/lineups?gameId=558272 |title=Cape Verde 2–0 Togo |accessdate=19 October 2019 |publisher=ESPN}}</ref>

He was included in Cape Verde's squad for the delayed [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]] tournament.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/africa/59763245|title = Group a rivals name squads for Afcon|work = BBC Sport}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.ie/sport/soccer/international-soccer/its-a-special-moment-for-me-dubliner-roberto-lopes-hoping-for-more-afcon-success-after-opening-win-41224884.html|title= 'It's a special moment for me' – Dubliner Roberto Lopes hoping for more AFCON success after opening win|date=10 January 2022|work=Irish Independent|access-date=10 January 2022}}</ref>

He was part of the Cape Verdean squad under manager [[Bubista]] in the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations]] tournament, where the nation made an extraordinary run to the quarter finals.

In October 2025, Lopes was part of the Cape Verdean team that [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification|qualified]] for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] after a 3–0 win against [[Eswatini national football team|Eswatini]]. In doing so, Lopes became the second ever current [[League of Ireland]] player to qualify for the World Cup, a day after [[St Patrick's Athletic F.C.|St Patrick's Athletic]] goalkeeper [[Joseph Anang]] was part of the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]] squad that qualified.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.rte.ie/sport/soccer/2025/1013/1538362-delight-for-lopes-as-cape-verde-qualify-for-world-cup/|title=Delight for Pico Lopes as Cape Verde qualify for World Cup|date=13 October 2025|work=RTE Sport|accessdate=14 October 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.rte.ie/sport/soccer/2025/1013/1538401-im-probably-the-luckiest-person-in-the-world-lopes/|title='I'm probably the luckiest person in the world' - Pico Lopes on Cape Verde's 2026 World Cup qualification|date=13 October 2025|work=RTE Sport|accessdate=14 October 2025}}</ref>

